                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="12894895" author="jbellis" created="Tue, 3 Aug 2010 14:53:24 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;the right fix is to remove the instanceof check in DatacenterShardStrategy instead &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12894909" author="slebresne" created="Tue, 3 Aug 2010 15:49:17 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;You&apos;re right. Attaching patch that just do that. I guess it would nice to get an InvalidRequestException when you try to insert a keyspace with a strategy incompatible with your snitch. But maybe the first move would be to make the snitch configuration per keyspace ?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12894910" author="jbellis" created="Tue, 3 Aug 2010 15:50:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;committed&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12894913" author="jbellis" created="Tue, 3 Aug 2010 15:55:22 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I don&apos;t think it makes sense for &quot;which node is closer&quot; to depend on what keyspace you&apos;re talking about&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12895246" author="hudson" created="Wed, 4 Aug 2010 13:25:31 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Integrated in Cassandra #509 (See &lt;a href=&quot;http://hudson.zones.apache.org/hudson/job/Cassandra/509/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://hudson.zones.apache.org/hudson/job/Cassandra/509/&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;br/&gt;
    remove instanceof checks for AbstractRackAwareSnitch.  patch by Sylvain Lebresne; reviewed by jbellis for &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-1349&quot; title=&quot;DynamicEndpointSnitch should implement AbstractRackAwareSnitch, not AbstractEndpointSnitch&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-1349&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-1349&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
